CatDescriptText: Oliver Nelson (1932-1975) played Hard Bop, and Post-Bop jazz.  His professional career as a musician began in 1947, with the Jeter-Pillars Orchestra.  By the time he moved to Los Angeles in 1967 he was well known as a composer, and he began working in the Hollywood studios, writing for television and movies.
